Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a light-brown pottery vessel, interior very worn, exterior covered with a cream-coloured slip and very faint traces of one line of black-painted hieratic text dated year 11, apparently no other text but presumably from a commodity label.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393189) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393189)
